abstract: >-
  This repository contains complete code, data, and analyses demonstrating that 
  quantum coherence mechanisms explain the 40-year "acute protective paradox" 
  in HIV neuroscience. We show that inflammatory noise correlation length (Î¾) 
  modulates neuronal metabolism through microtubule quantum coherence, with 
  shorter correlation lengths providing paradoxical neuroprotection during acute 
  HIV infection. Includes Bayesian v3.6 analysis (primary results), independent 
  enzyme kinetics validation, regional evolutionary analysis, and complete MRS 
  data from published studies.
